<biogHist>
<abstract>Riverina Juvenile Justice Centre at Wagga Wagga was established by the Department of Youth and Community Services in 1984. In 1991 it was transferred to the Department of Juvenile Justice. It has a capacity for 45 detainees. Riverina Juvenile Justice Centre is still operating in 2013.</abstract>
<p>Riverina Juvenile Justice Centre was run by the Department of Juvenile Justice after that department was created in 1990.</p>
<p>Riverina Juvenile Justice Centre was mentioned in the Bringing Them Home Report (1997) as an institution that housed Indigenous children removed from their families.</p>
